{
  "text": "An authentication method for a multimodal biometric system identification using two features i.e. face and palmprint has been presented by M.Nageshkumar et al. [CITATION_1] . The technique was created for application where the training data includes a face and palmprint. Mixing the palmprint and face features has improved the robustness of the person authentication. The final assessment was done by fusion at matching score level architecture where features vectors were formed independently for query measures and are then evaluated to the enrolment template, which were saved during database preparation. Multimodal biometric system was expanded through fusion of face and palmprint recognition.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "11812977"
